NoiSpecificProblem ::= TEXTUAL-CONVENTION STATUS current DESCRIPTION "The specific problem provides further qualification of the alarm than probable cause. It shall be used to classify the fault situation in the Network Element. Specific problem represents a fault specific integer value which shall be unique within the context of the Network Element. The Network Element shall not use the same specific problem for two distinct fault situations." SYNTAX Integer32 (1..2147483647)
NoiSystemDistinguishedName ::= TEXTUAL-CONVENTION DISPLAY-HINT "400t" STATUS current DESCRIPTION "The System Distinguished Name (SDN) identified the alarming object representing the resource where the fault occurs. The SDN represents the unique Distinguished Name of the instance within the scope of the system or Network Element (sometimes referred to as Local Distinguished Name). The required format is according to Nokia Distinguished Name syntax, for example SMSC-South/LNK-1" SYNTAX OCTET STRING (SIZE (0..1200))
NoiAlarmUUID ::= TEXTUAL-CONVENTION DISPLAY-HINT "384t" STATUS current DESCRIPTION "The Alarm Univerally Unique Identifier is an optional unique identifier of the alarm instance across different agents. Maximum length is 128 characters." SYNTAX OCTET STRING (SIZE (0..384))
